    <h1>How to Submit a Blog Post</h1>
    
    <p>
      We welcome contributions from the community! Our blog is fully open-source, 
      and anyone can submit a post via GitHub Pull Request.
    </p>
    
    <hr>
    
    <h2>Quick Start</h2>
    
    <ol>
      <li><strong>Fork</strong> the <a href="https://github.com/{{ site.repo }}" target="_blank">repository</a></li>
      <li><strong>Copy</strong> <code>content/blogs/0template.md</code> to <code>content/blogs/your-title.md</code></li>
      <li><strong>Edit</strong> your copied file with your blog content</li>
      <li><strong>Open</strong> a Pull Request</li>
      <li><strong>Community reviews</strong> your post</li>
      <li><strong>Merged = Published!</strong></li>
    </ol>
    
    <h2>Blog Template</h2>
    
    <p>Use the ready-to-copy template file:</p>
    <pre><code>cp content/blogs/0template.md content/blogs/your-title.md</code></pre>
    <p>Then edit the copied file and replace all placeholder values/content.</p>
    
    <p>If you prefer, here is the same template inline:</p>
    
