    <h2>Guidelines</h2>
    
    <ul>
      <li>Write about tech, learning, open-source, or community topics</li>
      <li>Keep it respectful and constructive</li>
      <li>Include code examples where helpful</li>
      <li>Use clear, descriptive titles</li>
      <li>Add a thumbnail image if possible (16:9 ratio recommended)</li>
      <li>Images should be added to <code>/src/assets/images/</code></li>
    </ul>
    
    <h2>File Naming</h2>
    
    <p>Name your file using kebab-case:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><code>getting-started-with-rust.md</code></li>
      <li><code>my-open-source-journey.md</code></li>
      <li><code>My Blog Post.md</code> (Avoid spaces)</li>
      <li><code>post1.md</code> (Avoid generic names)</li>
    </ul>
    
    <h2>Review Process</h2>
    
    <ol>
      <li>Open your Pull Request</li>
      <li>Maintainers will review for quality and guidelines</li>
      <li>You may receive feedback or suggestions</li>
      <li>Once approved, your PR is merged</li>
      <li>GitHub Actions builds and deploys automatically</li>
      <li>Your blog is live within minutes!</li>
    </ol>
    
